<refnamediv><refname>imclearborder</refname><refpurpose>Remove foreground objects connected to the image border.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>bwout = imclearborder(image)
bwout = imclearborder(image, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>A 2D binary or numeric image. Nonzero values are foreground.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para>4 or 8 pixel connectivity. The default is 8.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>bwout</term><listitem><para>A boolean image with border-connected foreground objects removed.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imclearborder</function> keeps only foreground components that are completely separated from all four image borders under the selected connectivity.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = zeros(9, 9) == 1;
image(1, 2) = %t;
image(4:6, 4:6) = %t;
clean = imclearborder(image);
imshow(clean);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
